            <thetext>At least two things to evaluate for the bugzilla system:

* If possible add a prominent section to the emails that are sent out to reporters once a bug is moved to the &quot;resolved&quot; state, to encourage a retest and - if successful - have them explicitly mark the bug as &quot;verified&quot;

* If a bug has been &quot;resolved&quot; but not &quot;verified&quot; within a reasonable time span (maybe 3-5 days), is it possible to automatically send out reminder emails (&quot;whining&quot;)?

Other ideas to collaborate closer with reporters on verifying and ultimatively closing bugs are welcome.</thetext>
